<title type="html"><![CDATA[5/3 (Thurs.) Sunshine in the rain / Stoneman Douglas High School shooting (Host: Howard)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=162&amp;p=176#p176"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Section I</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Sunshine in the rain</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5iDkLR6pEQE" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5iDkLR6pEQE</a><br /><br />When I'm in Berlin you're off to London<br />當我在柏林，你正前往倫敦<br />When I'm in New York you're doing Rome<br />當我抵達紐約，你卻到了羅馬<br />All those crazy nights we spend together<br />那些我們共度的瘋狂夜晚<br />As voices on the phone<br />如今只剩下停留在答錄機的聲音<br /><br />Wishing we could be more telepathic<br />祈求我們能更心電感應<br />Tired of the nights I sleep alone<br />厭倦我一人孤枕難眠<br />Wishing we could redirect the traffic<br />祈求我們能改變交流溝通方式<br />And we find ourselves at home<br />在家遇見彼此<br /><br />Can you feel the raindrops in the desert?<br />你能感覺到沙漠甘霖嗎?<br />Have you seen the sunrays in the dark?<br />你曾見過黑暗中的光芒嗎?<br />Do you feel my love when I'm not present?<br />當我不在你身旁，你能感覺到我的愛嗎?<br />Standing by your side while miles apart<br />我的愛與你相伴,當相隔數哩<br /><br />Sunshine in the rain<br />陽光閃耀的雨天<br />Love is still the same<br />愛仍舊不變<br />Sunshine in the rain<br />陽光閃耀著雨天<br />Sunshine in the rain<br />陽光閃耀著雨天<br />Love is still the same<br />愛仍舊不變<br />Sunshine in the rain<br />陽光閃耀的雨天<br /><br />Even if we call the highest power<br />即使用盡全力相互呼喚<br />We can only do one town a time<br />我們只能做那麼一次<br />Words are not enough action speaks louder<br />諾言是不夠  行動才實際<br />Second time around<br />破鏡重圓 / 但是回音卻會久久不散 / <br />--------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />This song is flexura primativus of <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #0000FF">蔡依林's 日不落<br /></span></span>1.Long distance love is a challenge to a loving couple? Even the modern facilities can't overcome the vital weakness?<br />2.Here are some tips for maintaining long distance relationship:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Long-Distance-Relationship-Work">http://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Long-Dist ... nship-Work</a><!-- m --><br />Which one of the 3 parts or which item do you think is more useful to maintain long distance relationship? Or you have your own different opinion?<br />3.Please correct and polish my Chinese translation of the English song with your reasons. Any criticism and guidance are welcome.<br /><br />--------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Section II</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Stoneman Douglas High School shooting</span><br /><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stoneman_Douglas_High_School_shooting" class="postlink">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stoneman_Douglas_High_School_shooting</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />1.Do you agree Florida Senator Marco Rubio said that &quot;most&quot; proposals on stricter gun laws &quot;would not have prevented&quot; this shooting nor &quot;any of those in recent history&quot; and that lawmakers should take action with &quot;focus on the violence part&quot; alongside guns?<br />2.How do you perceive &quot;when the NRA alleged that the ban on gun sales to people under 21 was unconstitutional because it violated the rights that the Second and Fourteenth Amendments conferred to 18- to 21-year-olds, who were classified as adults&quot;?<br />3.Should everybody who wants to own a gun or purchase large quantities of fertilizer be subject to a brain scan that detects psychopathic, unempathetic behavior?<br />4.After compare to Sun An Tso's (孫安佐) case , please give your opinion.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #0000FF">Reference : 孫安佐(狄鶯+孫鵬獨子): 美國媒體是如何報導? 與台灣媒體不同的地方? 文化差異? 重點不同? (#小如 211集 #ABCmsRoo)</span></span><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w20jkaEJKMA" class="postlink">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w20jkaEJKMA</a><br />Adjust the setting speed to 1.5 if you wanna get quicker understanding.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><br />The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Fri Apr 27, 2018 11:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
